		<td><b>Pokémon Crystal and Action Replay</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm curious about why this Pokémon Crystal freezes when leaving a town, entering a house or something like that (reloading maps or GFX data, dunno) with the Action Replay Xtreme attached and enabled until you disable it with the switch, even with no cheat enabled.
<br />The snapshot function and the game trainer still works. I thought the AR was designed to work transparently to the game running on the GameBoy
<br />
<br />Also, anyone knows how does this device works? Using NMIs or something?
<br />
<br />And a proposal: what about using the AR or GG to run code from a Gameboy Camera Save-RAM? There is 128kB of RAM, and data could be transferred using a GB&lt;-&gt;PC transfer cable and "Receive photo"

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


