	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are Master Codes for other RAM-only based systems (eg.: the DS), that indicates the AR where to put its bootloader. AFAIK the GBC AR doesn't require anyone for any game, because it simply disables the ROM (or SRAM?) from the game and puts there its own BIOS
<br />
<br />Oh, forgot something: it works well with Pokémon Gold and Silver with no Master Code
<br />
<br />EDIT: I've been searching with the bgb for reads on the 0000-0103 to see if the game checks the vectors but I haven't found anything useful
<br />
<br />There is one of these checks just after boot and before the initial "NINTENDO / GAME FREAK / CREATURES INC" screen. The screen remains black (so the pallettes have been already loaded) until you turn the AR off
<br />
<br />PS: Gameshark = Action Replay

		

		</td>
	</tr>
